text: Raimo Suikkanen (20 December 1942 - 22 January 2021) was a Finnish racing cyclist. He competed at the 1968 Summer Olympics and the 1972 Summer Olympics. He was born in Iitti, Finland. Suikkanen died on 22 January 2021, aged 78. ==References== Category:1942 births Category:2021 deaths Category:Olympians for Finland Category:Cyclists
